Preheat oven to 350 degrees Prepare 2 cookie sheets. Beat butter and sugars until creamy, then beat in the orange rind, almond extract and anise seed. Combine the flour, almonds and salt with a fork and beat this into the butter mixture. Chill the dough for at least 2 hours. Break off 1-inch pieces of dough and shape them into balls. Flatten them slightly and bake for 20 minutes. Cool for a few minutes on a cookie rack. Roll the cookies in the superfine sugar while they are still warm. Store in an airtight tin.